{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 15:29:22.401977", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting diagnosis report — SDN spine–leaf lab\nOverview\n- Topology (from provided description): single spine (spine_1), two leaves (leaf_1, leaf_2). Each leaf has two hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 (host_1_* on leaf_1; host_2_* on leaf_2). All switches on management net 20.0.0.0/24; SDN controller at 20.0.0.100.\n- Summary finding: management plane (control channel) is up (switches have management IPs and controllers are connected), but the data plane is partially down: leaf_1 is dropping data traffic and its access hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2) are isolated. Evidence indicates a high-priority blanket drop flow installed on leaf_1’s OpenFlow table is the primary cause.\n\nKey observations / evidence\n1) Controller connectivity and management plane\n- ovs-vsctl show on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: each bridge reports Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" with is_connected: true. Management IPs are present:\n  - spine_1: 20.0.0.1\n  - leaf_1: 20.0.0.5\n  - leaf_2: 20.0.0.6\n  (=> controller connectivity / management network appears healthy)\n\n2) OVS flow tables\n- leaf_1: ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1 returned a single (high-impact) flow:\n  - table=0, priority=100, n_packets=91376, actions=drop\n    - Interpretation: a blanket drop rule (no match fields shown — effectively matches traffic at table 0) is actively dropping a large number of packets on leaf_1.\n- leaf_2: ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_2 shows specific output rules (matching dl_src/dl_dst) but with zero packet counts; flows exist that forward traffic on leaf_2.\n- spine_1: ovs-ofctl dump-flows spine_1 shows forwarding entries with substantial packet counts (spine is forwarding).\n\n3) Interface / traffic counters\n- leaf_1 ifconfig/ip addr:\n  - Management eth12: inet 20.0.0.5 and large RX counters on eth12 (management traffic).\n  - Many other ethX interfaces show RX packets present but TX packets = 0 on those interfaces — i.e., the switch ports receive frames but are not transmitting them out (consistent with a drop action in datapath).\n- leaf_2 and spine_1 show healthy RX/TX counters on their data interfaces (they are forwarding).\n\n4) Host behavior and test pings\n- host_1_1 (10.0.0.1) and host_1_2 (10.0.0.2):\n  - ifconfig shows inet addresses and link UP, but RX packets are 0 (no inbound frames seen), TX only small (few) — consistent with being isolated and not receiving data plane frames.\n- host_2_1 (10.0.0.9) and host_2_2 (10.0.0.10):\n  - have significant RX counters.\n  - Ping from host_2_1 -> host_1_1 returned: \"From 10.0.0.9 icmp_seq=x Destination Host Unreachable\" (immediate local failure to reach host_1_1). This is consistent with ARP / L2 reachability failure to host_1_1 (not reachable across the network because leaf_1 is dropping).\n  - A direct ping host_2_1 -> host_2_2 (same leaf_2) in one test timed out (tool timeout); this appears to be separate/ambiguous — leaf_2 and spine flows show forwarding, so this timeout may be transient or test-timeout-related and needs re-checking.\n\nFault localization (devices impacted)\n- Primary faulty device: leaf_1 (OVS instance / bridge \"leaf_1\").\n  Evidence:\n  - OVS flow table on leaf_1 contains a high-priority drop flow with heavy packet count (n_packets ~ 91k) and no forwarding flows observed.\n  - leaf_1 bridge ports show frames are being received (RX counters) but not forwarded (TX counters 0) — consistent with dropping in datapath.\n  - Hosts connected to leaf_1 (host_1_1 and host_1_2) show no RX traffic and are unreachable from other hosts.\n- Impacted hosts:\n  - host_1_1 (10.0.0.1) — isolated\n  - host_1_2 (10.0.0.2) — isolated\n- Other devices (leaf_2, spine_1) appear operational (have forwarding flows and non-zero TX/RX).\n\nProbable root cause\n- A controller-programmed OpenFlow rule (or local switch flow) on leaf_1 is dropping data-plane traffic: the observed flow \"table=0, priority=100 actions=drop\" is actively dropping packets. Because the controller is connected, this drop flow was likely installed by the controller (or a local management process via ofproto) rather than being a result of controller disconnection.\n- The result is layer-2/L3 traffic on leaf_1's access ports is not forwarded: hosts attached to leaf_1 cannot be reached and ARP/ICMP fails.\n- Physical links and management plane are healthy (interfaces are up, management IPs respond, controller connection is present) — so this is a datapath policy/flow-programming issue, not a physical link failure.\n\nAdditional notes / ambiguous items\n- Leaf_2 and spine_1 show forwarding entries and active counters, so the problem is localized to leaf_1 rather than a global controller outage.\n- The ping from host_2_1 to host_2_2 timing out (tool timeout) is unexpected given leaf_2 appears functional; that single timeout is ambiguous and should be re-tested (could be transient, rate-limiting, or a test time-out). It does not contradict the primary diagnosis that leaf_1 is the primary fault.\n- get_reachability initial output contained many \"unknown\" entries — possibly due to the reachability probe being limited in this environment. The direct checks and OVS dumps above provide the strongest evidence.\n\nEvidence excerpts (commands run and key outputs)\n- ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1:\n  - cookie=0x0, duration=121.180s, table=0, n_packets=91376, n_bytes=5482560, idle_age=0, priority=100 actions=drop\n- ovs-vsctl show (leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1):\n  - Bridge leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 each report Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" is_connected: true\n- leaf_1 interface counters:\n  - Several ethX ports show RX > 0 but TX = 0; eth12 (management) is configured and has IP 20.0.0.5.\n- host ping:\n  - host_2_1 -> host_1_1: \"From 10.0.0.9 icmp_seq=1 Destination Host Unreachable\" (4/4 failures in test)\n\nConclusions\n- Network health: partially degraded. Management/control plane is up (controller connected), but data-plane forwarding on leaf_1 is broken.\n- Localized root cause: a blanket drop flow in leaf_1’s OpenFlow table is dropping traffic for that leaf, isolating host_1_1 and host_1_2.\n- Affected components: leaf_1 (primary), host_1_1 and host_1_2 (impacted hosts).\n\nRecommended next diagnostic data to collect (for confirmation; not remediation)\n- Check controller flow-mod logs for leaf_1 (to see which flow_mod created the drop rule and when).\n- ovs-ofctl dump-ports-desc / ovs-ofctl dump-ports on leaf_1 to see per-port stats and whether the drop matches specific ingress ports.\n- tcpdump on a leaf_1 access port (and on the host) for ARP/ICMP to see whether ARP requests are leaving the host and being dropped by leaf_1.\n- Re-run host-to-host pings (host_2_1 <-> host_2_2, and host_1_1 <-> host_1_2 locally) to confirm scope of isolation.\n\n(End of report)", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 26917, "output_tokens": 3989, "total_tokens": 30906, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 26752}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2176}}}
